subSubSection.paragraph:
Intraspecific variation of male and female copulatory organs.
Males: in some specimens embolus minimally shorter (
Fig. 66C
) and reaching less far distally than in others (
Figs 36A
, 
66B
). Tegulum sometimes slightly more “shouldered” in retrolatero-distal section (
Figs 36A
, 
66B
) than in others (
Fig. 66C
). Females: epigyne and epigynal windows (W) in some specimens slightly more elongated (
Fig. 73G
) than in others (
Fig. 36C
). Lateral margins of W after strongly coverging anterior-medially reaching further medially in some specimens (
Fig. 73G
) than in others (
Fig. 36C
). Connective ducts in some specimens slightly longer (
Fig. 77F
) than in others (
Fig. 36D
); secondary spermathecae in some specimens even narrower (
Fig. 77F
) than most others (
Fig. 36D
), but rarely slightly broader (not illustrated).
